						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar set up in the <hi rend="italic">garbhagṛiha</hi> of the Vēṇugōpālasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1312, Pramōda, Śrāvaṇa, ba. 8, Thursday, corresponding to 1390 A.D., August 4.</p>						

						<p>Seems to record a gift made by Bramuva, son of Jakkalakāchana to the god Bhuvanamaṅgaḷa-Gōpīnātha at Māndala, on the occasion of Śrī-Jayanti.</p>						

						</summary>
